stateDiagram-v2

    [*] --> Drafted

    Drafted : Drafted<br/>--------<br/>title written<br/>context drafted<br/>not yet under review

    Drafted --> Proposed : open for review<br/>(team notification)

    Proposed : Proposed<br/>--------<br/>under team review<br/>not yet binding<br/>discussion captured

    Proposed --> Accepted : team consensus<br/>(date + reviewer recorded)
    Proposed --> Drafted : feedback requires revision
    Proposed --> Rejected : decision not adopted<br/>(reason recorded)

    Accepted : Accepted<br/>--------<br/>decision binding<br/>implementation underway<br/>or completed

    Accepted --> Deprecated : approach no longer preferred<br/>(no replacement chosen)
    Accepted --> Superseded : replaced by ADR-NNN<br/>(bidirectional cross-link)

    Deprecated : Deprecated<br/>--------<br/>not preferred for new work<br/>existing usage may continue<br/>no formal replacement

    Deprecated --> Superseded : replacement ADR<br/>now exists

    Superseded : Superseded<br/>--------<br/>replaced by specific newer ADR<br/>cross-reference bidirectional<br/>document remains for history

    Rejected : Rejected<br/>--------<br/>decision not adopted<br/>reason recorded<br/>document remains as evidence<br/>of the alternative considered

    Superseded --> [*]
    Rejected --> [*]

    note right of Proposed
        Status changes append
        to document history with
        date and reason recorded.
        The document accumulates
        its own lifecycle log.
    end note

    note right of Superseded
        Bidirectional cross-link:
        superseded ADR points
        forward to successor;
        successor points back.
        Corpus stays navigable.
    end note
